Package: psc-graph
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ghostscript, ghostscript-doc, groff,
 html2ps, imagemagick, imagemagick-doc, mupdf, mupdf-tools, netpbm,
 psutils, python-reportlab, python-reportlab-doc, tesseract-ocr,
Description: Collection of packages for images and typesetting
 This package provides nothing itself, but depends on lots of packages
 that the maintainer finds valuable for handling images and doing page
 layout.  They are:
 .
   * ghostscript - kitchen sink for postscript
   * groff - a typesetter (more than just groff-base)
   * html2ps - render documents on a page
   * imagemagick - convert image formats
   * mupdf - to view PDF and XPS files
   * mupdf-tools - command line converters
   * netpbm - more image conversion
   * psutils - rearrange postscript pages
   * python-reportlab - for my OCR tool
   * tesseract-ocr - the best image-to-text
 .
 Their documentation is also included.
